            <h2>Best Time to Visit Jaipur</h2>
            <p>The ideal time for visiting Jaipur is from October until March because this period is pleasant and can be used for sightseeing. Temperatures during the period range from 15°C to 25°C, hence making it suitable for activities outdoors in the city.</p>
            <p>However, between July and September, there are heavy rains that inhibit movement, while the summer months (April–June) have high heat levels with temperatures reaching above 40°C.</p>

            <h3>Top Five Tourist Spots in Jaipur</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><b>Amber Fort</b> – Possessing a beautiful fusion of Hindu and Mughal architecture, it serves up a 360-degree view of the surrounding mountains.</li>
                <li><b>City Palace</b> – A stunning set of buildings that is teeming with delicate details and royal splendour.</li>
                <li><b>Hawa Mahal</b> – This iconic edifice has an exceptional front with many small doors for use by the around-looking street life, but it is not seen by everyone.</li>
                <li><b>Jantar Mantar</b> – The 18th-century astronomical observatory features remarkable tools employed for astronomical observation and timekeeping.</li>
                <li><b>Nahargarh Fort</b> – Perched atop Aravalli Hills stands this fort that gives breathtaking sunset views over Jaipur city below. Photography enthusiasts will find it ideal as well as those interested in historical sites.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Travel Plan to Guide You</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Day 1:</b> Come to Jaipur, look at Hawa Mahal and discover what is so different about its facade. Eat local roadside food.</li>
                <li><b>Day 2:</b> Go to Amber Fort for an entire day – enjoy an elephant ride and behold the stunning scenery.</li>
                <li><b>Day 3:</b> Visit City Palace as an introduction to Jaipur who was a king once; it contains museums that reflect royal history in terms of artefacts while some buildings showcase exquisite architectural designs.</li>
                <li><b>Day 4:</b> Jantar Mantar is where we find astonishing observational tools at this observatory in the evening and spend time at the local coffee house.</li>
                <li><b>Day 5:</b> Proceed for a trek up to Nahargarh Fort and behold amazing sunset sights, which make great photographs before leaving with lifetime experiences in mind.</li>
            </ul>

